title: C1_BOOTSTRAP
---
<<declare $heat_safety = 45>>
<<declare $community_trust = 40>>
<<declare $infrastructure_stability = 42>>
<<declare $vulnerable_risk = 68>>
<<declare $budget_reserve = 100>>

<<declare $current_day = 1>>
<<declare $days_remaining = 6>>
<<declare $heatwave_week_survived = false>>
<<declare $heatwave_week_failed = false>>
<<declare $day1_started = false>>

<<declare $quest_petition_done = false>>
<<declare $quest_grid_done = false>>
<<declare $quest_buddy_done = false>>
<<declare $quest_transit_done = false>>
<<declare $quest_shade_done = false>>
<<declare $quest_rowan_done = false>>
<<declare $quest_final_done = false>>

<<declare $met_maya = false>>
<<declare $met_daniel = false>>
<<declare $met_alvarez = false>>
<<declare $met_jae = false>>
<<declare $met_kai = false>>
<<declare $met_rowan = false>>

<<declare $maya_assigned = false>>
<<declare $daniel_assigned = false>>
<<declare $alvarez_assigned = false>>
<<declare $transit_assigned = false>>
<<declare $kai_assigned = false>>
<<declare $rowan_assigned = false>>

<<declare $maya_choice = 0>>
<<declare $daniel_choice = 0>>
<<declare $alvarez_choice = 0>>
<<declare $transit_choice = 0>>
<<declare $kai_choice = 0>>
<<declare $rowan_choice = 0>>

Narrator: Darkness. Then a ceiling fan hums above you.
Narrator: You wake up in the mayor's office with no memory of your old world.
Narrator: The digital wall clock reads 5:40 AM.
Narrator: Outside the window, heat haze blurs the streets and buses already run half empty.
Narrator: Today's forecast is 112F, with a night low of 94F.
Narrator: A stalled high-pressure dome has trapped heat over the city for 19 days.
Mayor: Where am I...?
Mayor: This office, this city, none of this looks familiar.
Mayor: Why is it this hot already? It feels like the air is burning.
Narrator: In the last 48 hours, emergency lines logged 312 heat distress calls.
Narrator: 68 residents were admitted for severe heat illness, and clinics are over capacity.
Narrator: Cooling costs doubled in two districts this week. Some families now choose between rent and air conditioning.
Narrator: This city gave you seven days. Day 7 is the hard deadline.
Maya: Easy. Sit up slowly.
Maya: Hi, Mayor. I'm Maya, community organizer for Library Block.
Maya: You crossed worlds last night. You are Heatwave City's new mayor now.
Maya: This role is not symbolic. Your choices decide who gets cooling, power, water, and safe nights.
Maya: We solve this without violence. We do it through policy, coordination, and showing up in the right places.
Maya: Before Day 1 starts, you must meet every district lead and hear the city directly.
Maya: Meet Daniel, Mrs. Alvarez, Jae, Kai, and Rowan. Listen first, then decide.
Maya: After that, come back to me. I will open the Day 1 response board.
<<set $met_maya = true>>
Mayor: Understood. I need the full picture before I sign anything.
Assistant Lin: Orientation phase started.
Assistant Lin: Follow the objective marker and meet each leader.
Assistant Lin: Each leader will explain their district risk and what they need from you.
<<stop>>
===

title: C1_CH1_RED_ALERT
---
<<if $day1_started == false>>
    <<if $met_rowan == false>>
        City Clerk Rowan: Hi Mayor. Rowan here, city clerk at Mayor Plaza.
        City Clerk Rowan: My job is to track what the numbers hide.
        City Clerk Rowan: This crisis is not only temperature. It is unequal access to protection.
        City Clerk Rowan: Wealthier blocks can buy cooling. Poorer blocks absorb the worst risk and longer outages.
        City Clerk Rowan: Your week is judged by Heat Safety, Community Trust, Infrastructure Stability, and Vulnerable Risk.
        City Clerk Rowan: Meet every lead, then return to Maya to start Day 1 formally.
        <<set $met_rowan = true>>
        <<stop>>
    <<else>>
        City Clerk Rowan: You have my report already, Mayor.
        City Clerk Rowan: Finish the remaining introductions, then begin Day 1 with Maya.
        <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<else>>
    <<if $quest_rowan_done>>
        City Clerk Rowan: City alert audit is complete.
        City Clerk Rowan: Messaging gaps are now visible on your dashboard.
        -> Ask what to do now
            City Clerk Rowan: Finish any open field tasks, then submit Final Audit on Day 7.
            <<stop>>
        -> Close briefing
            <<stop>>
    <<elseif $rowan_assigned>>
        City Clerk Rowan: Communication plan is assigned.
        City Clerk Rowan: Inspect the City Alert Audit marker in Mayor Plaza to validate rollout.
        <<stop>>
    <<else>>
        City Clerk Rowan: Daily briefing.
        City Clerk Rowan: Today is 112F, with nighttime lows still above 94F.
        City Clerk Rowan: 1 in 4 households in old blocks report unsafe indoor heat after midnight.
        City Clerk Rowan: Our weak point is city communication. Too many residents never receive alerts in time.
        City Clerk Rowan: Pick one communication policy, then inspect the City Alert Audit site.
        -> Plan A: Multilingual alerts + door-to-door volunteers
            <<set $rowan_assigned = true>>
            <<set $rowan_choice = 1>>
            City Clerk Rowan: Good. Verify neighborhood coverage at the audit marker.
            <<stop>>
        -> Plan B: SMS alerts only
            <<set $rowan_assigned = true>>
            <<set $rowan_choice = 2>>
            City Clerk Rowan: Lower cost, weaker reach. Confirm response gaps on site.
            <<stop>>
        -> Plan C: Delay communication update
            <<set $rowan_assigned = true>>
            <<set $rowan_choice = 3>>
            City Clerk Rowan: Then inspect confusion points directly before this gets worse.
            <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<endif>>
===

