title: C1_SIDE_PETITION_START
---
<<if $day1_started == false>>
    <<if $met_daniel && $met_alvarez && $met_jae && $met_kai && $met_rowan>>
        Maya: Good. You met every district lead.
        Maya: Then listen carefully. Starting now, this is Day 1.
        Maya: Your goal this week is simple to say and hard to do: keep people alive fairly.
        Maya: Assign policy, visit field sites yourself, and prove each action on the ground.
        -> Start Day 1 now
            <<set $day1_started = true>>
            Maya: Day 1 has started. We begin with cooling access.
            <<stop>>
    <<else>>
        Maya: Hi again, Mayor. We start Day 1 only after you meet every leader.
        Maya: This week will punish rushed decisions, so hear the district reports first.
        Maya: Then come back to me and we lock your first policy.
        <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<elseif $quest_petition_done>>
    Maya: Cooling petition work is already verified in the field. Thank you for showing up in person.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<elseif $maya_assigned>>
    Maya: Policy is assigned. Go inspect the Library cooling hall to validate rollout.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<else>>
    Maya: We have 4,300 households in the south blocks without reliable cooling.
    Maya: The heatwave is no longer just weather, it is a survival gap.
    Maya: Over 120 seniors were moved to corridor floors last night because rooms held heat.
    Maya: Choose a cooling policy and then verify it yourself at the field site.
    -> Open 3 temporary cooling centers tonight
        <<set $maya_assigned = true>>
        <<set $maya_choice = 1>>
        Maya: Good. Go to the Library field marker and inspect operations.
        <<stop>>
    -> Delay and collect more studies first
        <<set $maya_assigned = true>>
        <<set $maya_choice = 2>>
        Maya: If we delay, be ready to face people directly at the site.
        <<stop>>
    -> Home cooling subsidy only
        <<set $maya_assigned = true>>
        <<set $maya_choice = 3>>
        Maya: Then verify who still gets left out at the field site.
        <<stop>>
<<endif>>
===

title: C1_SIDE_PETITION_STAGE2
---
Maya: Return after your field check if you want to tune this policy.
-> Close
    <<stop>>
===

title: C1_SIDE_GRID_START
---
<<if $day1_started == false>>
    <<if $met_daniel == false>>
        Daniel: Hi Mayor. I'm Daniel, lead grid engineer in South District.
        Daniel: You need my pre-Day-1 brief.
        Daniel: Peak load reached 96 percent yesterday. That is near cascading failure range.
        Daniel: Night cooling demand keeps climbing while old transformers overheat.
        Daniel: If two clusters fail together, we lose signals, clinic feeders, and some pump stations.
        Daniel: Meet the other leaders, then come back after Day 1 starts for policy selection.
        <<set $met_daniel = true>>
        <<stop>>
    <<else>>
        Daniel: My orientation report is logged, Mayor.
        Daniel: Finish the other meetings first, then we'll choose a grid strategy.
        <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<elseif $quest_grid_done>>
    Daniel: Grid policy is already validated on site.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<elseif $daniel_assigned>>
    Daniel: Plan is assigned. Meet me at the transformer block marker and inspect failures directly.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<else>>
    Daniel: Our peak load passed 96 percent of safe capacity yesterday.
    Daniel: The grid was designed 30 years ago, before this level of nightly AC demand.
    Daniel: If two transformer clusters fail together, hospitals and signals can drop.
    -> Plan A: Rolling restrictions
        <<set $daniel_assigned = true>>
        <<set $daniel_choice = 1>>
        Daniel: Then inspect neighborhood outages in person.
        <<stop>>
    -> Plan B: Temporary solar and battery hubs
        <<set $daniel_assigned = true>>
        <<set $daniel_choice = 2>>
        Daniel: Then verify installation at the field marker.
        <<stop>>
    -> Plan C: Delay intervention
        <<set $daniel_assigned = true>>
        <<set $daniel_choice = 3>>
        Daniel: Then at least visit the site and witness the risk yourself.
        <<stop>>
<<endif>>
===

title: C1_SIDE_BUDDY_START
---
<<if $day1_started == false>>
    <<if $met_alvarez == false>>
        Mrs. Alvarez: Hello Mayor. I'm Mrs. Alvarez from Old Quarter.
        Mrs. Alvarez: Thank you for coming before Day 1 starts.
        Mrs. Alvarez: Heat risk is not equal. Seniors and chronic patients decline fastest at night.
        Mrs. Alvarez: Some neighbors avoid cooling centers because they fear paperwork, crowds, or shame.
        Mrs. Alvarez: We need trust, transport, and check-ins, not only one announcement.
        Mrs. Alvarez: Hear everyone first. Then come back with policy once Day 1 opens.
        <<set $met_alvarez = true>>
        <<stop>>
    <<else>>
        Mrs. Alvarez: You already heard us, Mayor.
        Mrs. Alvarez: Please finish meeting the other leaders before Day 1 begins.
        <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<elseif $quest_buddy_done>>
    Mrs. Alvarez: You came to our buildings yourself. People noticed.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<elseif $alvarez_assigned>>
    Mrs. Alvarez: We are waiting for your field visit in Old Quarter homes.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<else>>
    Mrs. Alvarez: In my building alone, 17 elders live without working air conditioning.
    Mrs. Alvarez: We now sleep in shifts to check who is still breathing normally.
    Mrs. Alvarez: The heat after midnight is worse than noon for heart patients.
    -> Fund a Heatwave Buddy system
        <<set $alvarez_assigned = true>>
        <<set $alvarez_choice = 1>>
        Mrs. Alvarez: Then come inspect home visits directly.
        <<stop>>
    -> Hotline only
        <<set $alvarez_assigned = true>>
        <<set $alvarez_choice = 2>>
        Mrs. Alvarez: Then stand at the site and hear response times.
        <<stop>>
    -> No city support
        <<set $alvarez_assigned = true>>
        <<set $alvarez_choice = 3>>
        Mrs. Alvarez: Then at least witness what people face.
        <<stop>>
<<endif>>
===

