title: C1_CH2_HEATWAVE_WEEK
---
<<if $day1_started == false>>
    <<if $met_jae == false>>
        Station Worker Jae: Hi Mayor, I'm Jae, station operations lead at Transit Hub.
        Station Worker Jae: Orientation note from Transit Hub.
        Station Worker Jae: Platform surface hit 131F yesterday. Workers still had to run shifts.
        Station Worker Jae: If transit fails, low-income families lose cooling access and wages together.
        Station Worker Jae: We need shade, water points, and stable signals during peak heat hours.
        Station Worker Jae: Meet everyone first. Day 1 policy selection comes after Maya's kickoff.
        <<set $met_jae = true>>
        <<stop>>
    <<else>>
        Station Worker Jae: Report delivered, Mayor. Continue orientation.
        <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<elseif $quest_transit_done>>
    Station Worker Jae: Transit heat mitigation is already completed.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<elseif $transit_assigned>>
    Station Worker Jae: Assignment is active. Inspect the platform field marker.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<else>>
    Station Worker Jae: Platform surface reached 131F yesterday at 1 PM.
    Station Worker Jae: Two commuters collapsed, and train delays trapped people in heat pockets.
    Station Worker Jae: If transit cooling fails, low-income workers lose both income and safety.
    -> Prioritize clinic and signal feeders
        <<set $transit_assigned = true>>
        <<set $transit_choice = 1>>
        Station Worker Jae: Then inspect platform flow at noon heat.
        <<stop>>
    -> Cooling tents and water points
        <<set $transit_assigned = true>>
        <<set $transit_choice = 2>>
        Station Worker Jae: Then verify deployment at the field marker.
        <<stop>>
    -> Limited upgrade, split budget
        <<set $transit_assigned = true>>
        <<set $transit_choice = 3>>
        Station Worker Jae: Then inspect which stops are still exposed.
        <<stop>>
<<endif>>
