title: C1_CH3_SHADE_CITY_START
---
<<if $day1_started == false>>
    <<if $met_kai == false>>
        Kai: Hi Mayor. I'm Kai, urban climate planner from the Cooling Center team.
        Kai: Pre-Day-1 planning note.
        Kai: This city stores heat because concrete outnumbers trees block by block.
        Kai: Heat maps already show up to 9F difference between rich and poor districts.
        Kai: We need cooler routes, shade corridors, and fair access, not just more AC load.
        Kai: Meet all leads first. Then we choose strategy when Day 1 officially starts.
        <<set $met_kai = true>>
        <<stop>>
    <<else>>
        Kai: My orientation brief is complete, Mayor.
        Kai: Finish the rest, then return to Maya to launch Day 1.
        <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<elseif $quest_shade_done>>
    Kai: Shade corridor package is already validated on site.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<elseif $kai_assigned>>
    Kai: Assignment is active. Inspect the cooling corridor field marker.
    -> Close
        <<stop>>
<<else>>
    Kai: Rich blocks have tree shade and cross-ventilation, poor blocks have bare concrete.
    Kai: Our heat maps show up to 9F difference between neighborhoods at the same hour.
    Kai: We need structural cooling, not only short-term AC demand.
    -> Shade-first plan (trees + awnings + cool corridors)
        <<set $kai_assigned = true>>
        <<set $kai_choice = 1>>
        Kai: Good. Walk the corridor with me and verify route access.
        <<stop>>
    -> AC subsidy-first plan
        <<set $kai_assigned = true>>
        <<set $kai_choice = 2>>
        Kai: Then inspect overload pressure at the corridor marker.
        <<stop>>
    -> Hybrid plan
        <<set $kai_assigned = true>>
        <<set $kai_choice = 3>>
        Kai: Then verify both shade and cooling access in person.
        <<stop>>
<<endif>>
